and you don't put a hose

00:45:01.650 --> 00:45:04.100
you know, through your
nostril or through your ear

00:45:04.100 --> 00:45:06.190
or through some other
orifice in your body,

00:45:06.190 --> 00:45:10.260
you inhale air and it's then
distributed via the lungs

00:45:10.260 --> 00:45:12.350
to the cells in your blood stream,

00:45:12.350 --> 00:45:15.380
and then it's distributed to
all the organs of your body.

00:45:15.380 --> 00:45:19.460
Every cell and organ in your
body needs light information,

00:45:19.460 --> 00:45:21.300
and the way to get that light information

00:45:21.300 --> 00:45:22.200
to all those cells,

00:45:22.200 --> 00:45:24.510
because you have a thick skull

00:45:24.510 --> 00:45:29.230
and the inside of you is
dark inside your skin,

00:45:29.230 --> 00:45:30.810
there's no sunlight getting in there,

00:45:30.810 --> 00:45:32.760
is by viewing sunlight with your eyes

00:45:32.760 --> 00:45:35.550
at the two times of day
that I'm referring to, okay?

00:45:35.550 --> 00:45:37.420
That's the only route.

00:45:37.420 --> 00:45:39.050
There was a study published in "Science,"

00:45:39.050 --> 00:45:40.930
an excellent journal,

00:45:40.930 --> 00:45:43.230
well over 10 years ago,

