you can explore intermittent
and circadian fasting,

00:55:33.360 --> 00:55:35.580
so to speak, through Satchin's literature,

00:55:35.580 --> 00:55:36.413
we'll talk about that,

00:55:36.413 --> 00:55:38.450
we might even get Satchin
in here if we're lucky

00:55:38.450 --> 00:55:39.860
at some point in the future,

00:55:39.860 --> 00:55:43.370
but you can actually use
light to wake up earlier.

00:55:43.370 --> 00:55:46.440
Jamie Zeitzer and colleagues
did a beautiful study

00:55:46.440 --> 00:55:51.440
showing that, if you turn on
the lights before waking up,

00:55:51.680 --> 00:55:54.850
so around 45 minutes to
an hour before waking up,

00:55:54.850 --> 00:55:56.400
even if your eyelids are closed,

00:55:56.400 --> 00:55:58.683
provided you're not under the covers,

00:55:59.900 --> 00:56:01.760
